    javascript is backward compatible. this means that newer versions of the language can run on older versions of the language. this is because the newer versions of the language are based on the older versions of the language.

    babel is a tool that can be used to convert es6 code to es5 code. this is useful because not all browsers support es6 code. babel can be used to convert es6 code to es5 code so that it can run on all browsers.


     

